    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="361"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/490</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Swedish Minister of Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_HJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hellner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1918</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 27.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I hereby have the honour to bring to Your
                    Excellency’s notice that His Majesty’s Government have decided to send Mr.
                        <persName>A. R. Nordvall</persName>
                    <pb facs="0447" n="1281" xml:id="pg_1281"/> to Washington in the capacity of a
                    commissioner of His Majesty’s Government to the United States of America.</p>
                <p>As Your Excellency would remember, my predecessor in the office of Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs had the advantage to introduce Mr. <persName>Nordvall</persName>
                    to Your Excellency on the occasion of the latter’s visit to Washington as a
                    delegate of His Majesty’s Government for certain commercial negotiations.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName>Nordvall</persName> is now proceeding to the United States with a
                    commission to organize the purchase of goods for export to Sweden in conformity
                    with the recently signed general agreement between Sweden and the United States
                    and their allies and to negotiate for the granting of licences for facilitating
                    the export of such goods and to deal with other matters in connection
                    therewith.</p>
                <p>I allow myself to take this opportunity of saying that His Majesty’s Government
                    would feel most particularly obliged, if also on this occasion Your Excellency
                    would extend to Mr. <persName>Nordvall</persName> the same kindness and courtesy
                    as was continuously shown him on his previous visit to the United States.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_HJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hellner</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
